WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:32.070 --> 00:01:36.830
Fool of a Lord

3
00:01:38.750 --> 00:01:39.950
B-Buggy!

4
00:01:39.950 --> 00:01:41.290
The captain...!

5
00:01:41.290 --> 00:01:42.830
It's Captain Roger!

6
00:01:50.920 --> 00:01:53.340
They're back!

7
00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:56.470
They're flashily back!

8
00:01:57.430 --> 00:02:00.980
Captain!

9
00:02:21.950 --> 00:02:27.710
When Roger returned from Laugh Tale,
Redtaro asked him something...

10
00:02:27.710 --> 00:02:29.710
and broke into tears.

11
00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:40.930
The birth of the King of the Pirates
caused quite a stir the world over...

12
00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:44.560
and the Marines began
to take drastic measures.

13
00:02:45.940 --> 00:02:49.150
"Wealth, fame, power...

14
00:02:49.150 --> 00:02:51.690
The man who attained everything...

15
00:02:51.690 --> 00:02:54.860
The King of the Pirates, Gold Roger"!

16
00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:59.700
It should be Gol D. Roger!

17
00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:04.250
But "King of the Pirates" has
a pretty nice ring to it.

18
00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:10.250
Now I understand why the World Government
would want to cover up your name.

19
00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:16.470
The world referred to everything
that Roger had obtained...

20
00:03:16.470 --> 00:03:21.430
as the great treasure One Piece!

21
00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:23.350
They don't know anything!

22
00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:29.810
But your notoriety has
everyone after you, Roger!

23
00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:35.820
Take down Roger!

24
00:03:42.870 --> 00:03:45.500
Find Roger!

25
00:03:45.500 --> 00:03:47.710
Plunder his treasure!

26
00:03:47.710 --> 00:03:50.920
Gold Roger has everything!

27
00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:09.650
Looking back, it's all been miraculous.

28
00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:14.230
With such a limited life expectancy,
I can't believe I made it this far.

29
00:04:15.860 --> 00:04:18.610
I have nothing but gratitude to you guys!

30
00:04:20.870 --> 00:04:22.490
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

31
00:04:22.490 --> 00:04:25.830
Why are you speaking all
proper outta nowhere, Captain?!

32
00:04:25.830 --> 00:04:27.870
Don't make me blush, dummy!

33
00:04:27.870 --> 00:04:28.620
Dummy!

34
00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:41.970
Then I'll just say it!

35
00:04:41.970 --> 00:04:43.260
Lay it on us!

36
00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:44.720
We're ready!

37
00:04:54.820 --> 00:04:58.030
I am hereby disbanding the Roger Pirates!

38
00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:23.640
The birth is at hand...

39
00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:26.600
Our ruler will be born...

40
00:05:26.600 --> 00:05:29.980
Another will be born in a distant sea...

41
00:05:29.980 --> 00:05:35.980
Even the whales are happily anticipating
the day the two rulers shall meet again...

42
00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:42.950
We have been waiting for so long, too...

43
00:05:44.280 --> 00:05:46.030
Very soon...

44
00:05:46.030 --> 00:05:48.490
I'm sure it will go well this time...

45
00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:51.500
Ten until the birth.

46
00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:54.460
Another fifteen to grow.

47
00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:57.040
Who are you?!

48
00:05:57.590 --> 00:06:01.260
How can you talk so deep under the sea?!

49
00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:08.180
Hey, Sharley, when will
the Mermaid Princess be born?

50
00:06:08.180 --> 00:06:09.220
Ten!

51
00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:14.650
That voice...

52
00:06:15.980 --> 00:06:16.940
Voice?!

53
00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:19.530
I'm sure it was telling the truth.

54
00:06:19.530 --> 00:06:21.320
Someone will be born.

55
00:06:21.320 --> 00:06:22.820
And...

56
00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:25.240
that person will surpass us...

57
00:06:30.410 --> 00:06:33.750
We were just too early...

58
00:06:33.750 --> 00:06:35.500
The One Piece, huh?

59
00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:37.540
I wonder who will find it.

60
00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:41.710
That'll be my son, of course.

61
00:06:41.710 --> 00:06:43.050
You don't have a son.

62
00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:45.640
I'm gonna have one eventually!

63
00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:52.480
Alright! Let's drink!

64
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:55.390
We'll sail to a sea with no Marines!

65
00:06:55.390 --> 00:06:57.270
I'll be the first off the ship!

66
00:06:57.270 --> 00:07:00.230
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

67
00:07:04.610 --> 00:07:08.620
Men! Take Oden home next!

68
00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:11.160
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

69
00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:12.910
Of course!

70
00:07:14.580 --> 00:07:16.170
Oh, yeah, Oden!

71
00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:19.500
I'm thinking about meeting
Whitebeard before I die.

72
00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:23.840
Do you want him to send
Izo back to Wano, too?

73
00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:25.090
No...

74
00:07:26.340 --> 00:07:28.930
His place is with that crew now.

75
00:07:29.350 --> 00:07:33.520
Tell him to take care of Whitekichi.

76
00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:36.230
Alright, I will.

77
00:07:43.980 --> 00:07:46.700
After some words to Rayleigh...

78
00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:51.200
Roger's first mate, a man
known as the Dark King...

79
00:07:57.830 --> 00:08:01.460
Roger left the ship.

80
00:08:01.460 --> 00:08:06.340
He received a bundle of medicine
from the ship's doctor, Crocus.

81
00:08:07.220 --> 00:08:10.430
His illness was in its final stages...

82
00:08:10.970 --> 00:08:16.890
But this was a man's farewell,
so not a single tear was shed.

83
00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:21.860
Members of the Pirate King's crew...

84
00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:25.610
would never cry!

85
00:08:27.990 --> 00:08:33.410
Off the Coast

of Wano

86
00:08:36.660 --> 00:08:38.500
It still blows my mind!

87
00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:42.790
So many wrecked ships that
couldn't reach the country...

88
00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:44.590
Yeah...

89
00:08:44.590 --> 00:08:47.090
If you veer into the wrong current,

90
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:52.090
your ship will be destroyed before
even getting close to Wano.

91
00:08:52.090 --> 00:08:54.970
This isolation policy once served a purpose.

92
00:08:54.970 --> 00:09:00.440
But we must open these borders
before the day of Joyboy's arrival!

93
00:09:05.020 --> 00:09:08.360
Be well, guys!

94
00:09:11.660 --> 00:09:13.780
It is not like I was dying.

95
00:09:14.410 --> 00:09:17.870
So of course, we said goodbye smiling.

96
00:09:17.870 --> 00:09:20.750
Because we knew we would see
each other again some day!

97
00:09:30.260 --> 00:09:32.470
Oden!

98
00:09:32.470 --> 00:09:34.300
I missed you!

99
00:09:34.930 --> 00:09:36.810
You guys!

100
00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:38.560
Go, Hiyori!

101
00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:42.140
Toki!

102
00:09:42.140 --> 00:09:44.060
Momonosuke!

103
00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:45.360
Hiyori!

104
00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:51.070
I missed you all, too!

105
00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:56.990
You have grown so much, Momonosuke!

106
00:09:57.160 --> 00:10:00.410
Indeed! I am happy you are doing well, too!

107
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:05.670
You even have proper manners!

108
00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:09.880
Welcome back!

109
00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:13.090
You deadbeat.

110
00:10:14.010 --> 00:10:16.390
And where are your manners?!

111
00:10:17.010 --> 00:10:19.810
You think you deserve proper manners?!

112
00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:28.610
Lord Oden!

113
00:10:28.610 --> 00:10:30.730
Lord Oden! Welcome back!

114
00:10:30.730 --> 00:10:32.240
Lord Oden!

115
00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:34.410
I'm happy for you, Lady Otoki!

116
00:10:41.290 --> 00:10:44.330
I still seem to be quite popular!

117
00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:47.210
I had neglected the country for so long.

118
00:10:47.210 --> 00:10:49.590
I thought they would be more critical of me...

119
00:10:49.590 --> 00:10:53.090
Thank your wife, Lady Toki!

120
00:10:53.090 --> 00:10:55.470
She is a very wonderful person...

121
00:10:55.470 --> 00:10:58.350
When she recovered from her illness,

122
00:10:58.350 --> 00:11:01.270
she came down into town
and helped citizens every day.

123
00:11:01.270 --> 00:11:03.810
She has never acted
arrogantly as a daimyo's wife.

124
00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:08.360
She labored with everyone and cheerfully
shared the stories of your adventure.

125
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:13.440
Lady Toki and your children
are extremely popular in Kuri now!

126
00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:16.780
And they had nothing but praise for you.

127
00:11:17.910 --> 00:11:23.410
At some point, everyone stopped
speaking ill of your selfish behavior!

128
00:11:23.410 --> 00:11:24.960
I see!

129
00:11:24.960 --> 00:11:27.540
I am grateful, everyone!

130
00:11:27.540 --> 00:11:31.630
It is because we really do
love you! Right, children?

131
00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:36.380
I am jealous! I want to be loved, too!

132
00:11:39.600 --> 00:11:41.810
Kiku! I must tell you about Izo...

133
00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:46.560
Doggy and Kitty told me!
I am just glad that he is well.

134
00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:48.270
I see!

135
00:11:48.270 --> 00:11:52.070
By the way, what happened
to Denjiro and Ashura?

136
00:11:52.070 --> 00:11:54.030
I did not see them a year ago, either...

137
00:11:54.570 --> 00:11:58.820
Ashura is the new head of both the yakuza
and the mountain bandits in Kuri.

138
00:11:58.820 --> 00:12:00.700
He's been keeping them in check.

139
00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:05.960
Denjiro is wandering about,
borrowing money and paying it back.

140
00:12:06.750 --> 00:12:12.340
Wrangling bandits and borrowing money
do not sound like comfortable lifestyles.

141
00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:13.880
Indeed.

142
00:12:14.300 --> 00:12:19.010
There is another reason that
everyone is happy about your return.

143
00:12:20.090 --> 00:12:22.180
I will tell the story from the beginning.

144
00:12:22.720 --> 00:12:31.110
After you left, we worked alongside
the citizens to run Kuri without its daimyo.

145
00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:34.360
I see. I am sure it wasn't easy.

146
00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:36.400
And what of my father?

147
00:12:42.870 --> 00:12:44.120
Our lord, the shogun–

148
00:12:44.120 --> 00:12:45.580
I understand!

149
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:50.540
So he was unwell...

150
00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:56.920
What a shame that I could not
be with him in his final moments.

151
00:12:57.340 --> 00:13:00.340
The problem is the shogun's successor!

152
00:13:00.340 --> 00:13:05.680
Though we do not know why, your father,
Lord Sukiyaki, advocated for Orochi...

153
00:13:07.470 --> 00:13:10.640
Please lend me money!

154
00:13:12.060 --> 00:13:14.610
My confusion only grew as I listened to him.

155
00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.530
Orochi is like a little brother to me?!

156
00:13:17.530 --> 00:13:20.900
I only lent him money out of respect for Yasu.

157
00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:24.450
He never repaid even a single silver coin!

158
00:13:24.450 --> 00:13:28.330
I also learned that Orochi
is a descendant of the Kurozumi Clan,

159
00:13:28.330 --> 00:13:30.910
which has a history of stirring up trouble.

160
00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:37.130
Apparently, Kurozumi Orochi has taken
the title of shogun as my proxy.

161
00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:40.670
I am certain you saw them on your way here,

162
00:13:41.090 --> 00:13:46.260
but each region has several weapons factories
and supervisors who oversee the labor.

163
00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:49.390
And the men of each region
are forced to work there

164
00:13:49.390 --> 00:13:53.600
earning poverty wages by the shogun's order.

165
00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:55.400
Why is that?!

166
00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:58.570
Why does everyone listen
to someone like Orochi?!

167
00:13:58.570 --> 00:14:03.070
That is because he has the support
of a pirate named Kaido.

168
00:14:03.070 --> 00:14:05.410
His strength is truly monstrous!

169
00:14:05.410 --> 00:14:08.490
With his protection,
Orochi can do as he pleases!

170
00:14:08.490 --> 00:14:11.080
Right! We tried to fight back, but–

171
00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:13.000
Enough, Kin'emon!

172
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.710
Not another word!

173
00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:17.250
No, I must know what happened!

174
00:14:18.300 --> 00:14:19.340
Raizo!

175
00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:22.760
Take Lord Momonosuke
and Lady Hiyori out of the room!

176
00:14:23.880 --> 00:14:24.890
Pardon me!

177
00:14:27.810 --> 00:14:30.600
About half a year ago...

178
00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:34.810
a man refused to work at one of
the factories, so he and his family...

179
00:14:36.190 --> 00:14:37.980
were put to death!

180
00:14:39.360 --> 00:14:43.990
We could no longer stand idly by
after witnessing Orochi's cruelty,

181
00:14:43.990 --> 00:14:49.660
so we took up arms and marched to
Orochi's palace in the Flower Capital...

182
00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:55.580
But while we were away,
Kaido's men sneaked into Kuri behind us!

183
00:14:56.710 --> 00:14:58.710
Because of our negligence...

184
00:15:01.420 --> 00:15:07.470
they attacked Lord Momonosuke,
the Kozuki Clan's next heir after Lord Oden!

185
00:15:14.440 --> 00:15:15.440
In the end...

186
00:15:17.770 --> 00:15:23.740
the invasion was repelled by Kawamatsu
and Inuarashi, who stayed to guard the castle.

187
00:15:28.700 --> 00:15:32.540
But the one who protected him
from their first arrow attack...

188
00:15:34.620 --> 00:15:39.170
was Lady Toki, who threw herself in front of it!

189
00:15:39.460 --> 00:15:41.960
I am deeply sorry!

190
00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:46.340
Due to our reckless actions,
Lady Toki's leg was seriously wounded!

191
00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:49.970
We put your family members' lives in danger!

192
00:15:49.970 --> 00:15:51.890
I am sorry!

193
00:15:51.890 --> 00:15:54.890
I am so sorry!

194
00:15:54.890 --> 00:15:56.980
Let me see, Toki.

195
00:15:56.980 --> 00:15:58.600
Do not worry, Oden!

196
00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:00.310
It is already healed!

197
00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:11.370
You protected our son... You did so well!

198
00:16:13.660 --> 00:16:15.120
How it must have hurt!

199
00:16:17.330 --> 00:16:22.210
Wait, Oden! We will just invite another attack
if you lose your temper over something so trivial!

200
00:16:23.130 --> 00:16:24.880
T... T...

201
00:16:26.130 --> 00:16:28.840
Trivial?!

202
00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:32.470
Toki, dear...

203
00:16:32.470 --> 00:16:37.100
have you not heard the stories
of my younger days?

204
00:16:39.310 --> 00:16:42.900
I understand the way Orochi does things!

205
00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:46.780
All of you! Protect my family!

206
00:16:48.570 --> 00:16:49.660
Oden!

207
00:16:53.030 --> 00:16:55.950
Protect Kuri!

208
00:17:02.060 --> 00:17:06.630
I may not understand all of
the fine details, but one thing is for sure.

209
00:17:08.090 --> 00:17:10.430
A fool has taken control of Wano!

210
00:17:10.550 --> 00:17:14.720
A weak, cowardly fool,
backed by a powerful pirate,

211
00:17:14.720 --> 00:17:17.740
has taken advantage of
this country's isolation...

212
00:17:25.320 --> 00:17:28.150
and their goal...

213
00:17:29.400 --> 00:17:32.200
is to turn this country into hell!

214
00:17:53.300 --> 00:17:54.300
H-Hey!

215
00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:55.930
Y-Yeah!

216
00:17:55.930 --> 00:17:59.930
It's an emergency! Kozuki Oden
is heading toward the Flower Capital!

217
00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:02.020
Report to Lord Orochi immediately!

218
00:18:04.400 --> 00:18:05.770
Lord Orochi!

219
00:18:14.950 --> 00:18:16.070
Was that...?!

220
00:18:16.490 --> 00:18:17.780
Lord Oden?!

221
00:18:17.780 --> 00:18:20.040
Lord Oden has returned?!

222
00:18:20.040 --> 00:18:22.000
He's the true heir!

223
00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:24.170
Is he taking the place of shogun?!

224
00:18:25.420 --> 00:18:28.670
Orochi's reign is finally over!

225
00:18:31.210 --> 00:18:33.260
Shogun Orochi! Please evacuate!

226
00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:34.630
What?

227
00:18:34.630 --> 00:18:36.050
What are you talking about?!

228
00:18:36.050 --> 00:18:39.930
Kozuki Oden has invaded the castle!

229
00:18:47.810 --> 00:18:49.610
Orochi...

230
00:18:52.780 --> 00:18:56.160
W-Wait a minute! Lor– I mean, O-Oden!

231
00:18:56.700 --> 00:18:57.990
Think twice!

232
00:18:57.990 --> 00:19:00.910
If you slice me up, Kaido won't
just take it lying down!

233
00:19:02.910 --> 00:19:06.290
Think what'll happen to this country!

234
00:19:07.580 --> 00:19:09.460
Only after I have cut you down!

235
00:19:12.460 --> 00:19:13.630
I forgot...

236
00:19:14.300 --> 00:19:15.300
He's...

237
00:19:19.550 --> 00:19:21.260
He's crazy!

238
00:19:27.810 --> 00:19:30.570
Orochi!

239
00:19:30.570 --> 00:19:34.150
Don't do it!

240
00:19:58.220 --> 00:19:59.140
What the...?!

241
00:19:59.510 --> 00:20:01.600
What is this?!

242
00:20:03.410 --> 00:20:04.640
Is it glass?!

243
00:20:04.640 --> 00:20:05.770
No!

244
00:20:08.810 --> 00:20:12.190
Get out here, Orochi!

245
00:20:14.110 --> 00:20:17.240
Orochi!

246
00:20:20.370 --> 00:20:23.990
Do not be frightened, Lord Orochi...

247
00:20:25.450 --> 00:20:28.620
Trust my Barrier-Barrier technique.

248
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:29.040
Kurozumi Semimaru

A Biwa-Playing Priest

249
00:20:29.040 --> 00:20:29.080
Kurozumi Semimaru

A Biwa-Playing Priest

250
00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:32.090
Kurozumi Semimaru

A Biwa-Playing Priest

251
00:20:32.090 --> 00:20:36.420
This barrier will prevent any approach.

252
00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:39.760
Your strength means nothing, Oden!

253
00:20:41.390 --> 00:20:43.350
That's right.

254
00:20:43.350 --> 00:20:47.230
If you were a pirate,
you must be familiar with...

255
00:20:47.230 --> 00:20:51.980
the superhuman powers of the devil fruits!

256
00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:52.020
Kurozumi Higurashi

An Old Woman

257
00:20:52.020 --> 00:20:55.030
Kurozumi Higurashi

An Old Woman

258
00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:56.820
You have powers, then!

259
00:20:56.820 --> 00:20:58.110
That's right.

260
00:20:58.110 --> 00:21:00.950
But people in this country call it sorcery...

261
00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:05.740
Oden, if anger and violence were the answer,

262
00:21:05.740 --> 00:21:09.330
the daimyos from other regions
would already have done it!

263
00:21:09.330 --> 00:21:12.040
No one can kill me!

264
00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:21.180
Orochi!

265
00:21:22.430 --> 00:21:29.140
I heard, for whatever reason,
my father named you as a proxy shogun...

266
00:21:29.680 --> 00:21:31.810
until my return!

267
00:21:34.060 --> 00:21:37.440
And now, you will yield the throne to me!

268
00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:40.990
I had no intention of becoming
someone so important...

269
00:21:40.990 --> 00:21:44.700
but I know I can at least do better than you!

270
00:21:48.660 --> 00:21:51.500
Well, unfortunately,

271
00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:55.630
those weren't actually the words
of your father, Sukiyaki.

272
00:21:56.960 --> 00:21:58.510
What do you mean?

273
00:22:03.220 --> 00:22:06.850
Ah... It's good to have you back, Oden!

274
00:22:06.850 --> 00:22:08.680
What?! Father?!

275
00:22:08.680 --> 00:22:10.430
How are you alive...?

276
00:22:13.690 --> 00:22:17.570
All those daimyos and
other idiots were suckered by...

277
00:22:19.190 --> 00:22:20.150
...me!

278
00:22:21.610 --> 00:22:24.700
She used the Clone-Clone Fruit's
power to transform herself,

279
00:22:24.700 --> 00:22:26.780
and everyone fell for it!

280
00:22:29.080 --> 00:22:34.000
The whole country believed her lies
and let me have the shogun's post!

281
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:35.420
So...

282
00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:38.960
I'm under no obligation to give up my position!

283
00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:44.630
Now there's no way to know
what the real Sukiyaki was thinking...

284
00:22:44.970 --> 00:22:47.800
You bastard! What did you do to my father?!

285
00:22:47.800 --> 00:22:50.470
Did he really die of an illness?!

286
00:22:55.850 --> 00:22:57.610
Lord Oden!

287
00:22:58.150 --> 00:22:59.360
Lord Oden!

288
00:22:59.360 --> 00:23:00.730
Oden!

289
00:23:03.240 --> 00:23:05.910
Lord Oden!

290
00:23:09.910 --> 00:23:12.790
While the townsfolk were
gathered outside the castle

291
00:23:12.790 --> 00:23:15.460
to cheer for the return of the Kozuki Clan,

292
00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:18.460
poisoned arrows were loosed into the crowd.

293
00:23:18.460 --> 00:23:22.800
Two people were struck, and they
vomited blood before falling blind.

294
00:23:23.170 --> 00:23:26.050
The other townsfolk who took
shelter amidst the chaos...

295
00:23:28.350 --> 00:23:34.060
witnessed the terrifying sight of a dragon
in the dark sky over the castle.

296
00:23:40.570 --> 00:23:44.690
He was an incorrigible youth, but he became
Kuri's daimyo and went out to sea...

297
00:23:45.150 --> 00:23:48.780
and matched the strength of
the world's greatest pirates...

298
00:23:54.870 --> 00:23:59.130
Now, he's returned home stronger than ever.

299
00:23:59.130 --> 00:24:02.300
The unrivaled Kozuki Oden!

300
00:24:05.510 --> 00:24:09.510
Don't worry. Lord Oden will save this country.

301
00:24:11.010 --> 00:24:11.970
Lord Oden!

302
00:24:11.970 --> 00:24:14.640
Lord Oden! We were waiting for you!

303
00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:15.890
Lord Oden!

304
00:24:16.430 --> 00:24:22.320
He would surely be the savior of the people
and free them from this tyrannical rule...

305
00:24:22.320 --> 00:24:23.480
Lord Oden...?

306
00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:26.320
Lord Oden?

307
00:24:26.900 --> 00:24:30.120
But a few hours later, Kozuki Oden...

308
00:24:30.120 --> 00:24:34.120
had stripped down to his loincloth
in front of Shogun Orochi's castle...

309
00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:37.790
and began acting the fool.

310
00:24:40.580 --> 00:24:43.460
Orochi and Kaido's underlings laughed at him.

311
00:24:49.050 --> 00:24:51.760
♪ One, two, three... ♪

312
00:24:52.220 --> 00:24:57.810
After groveling in the dirt and earning a pitiful
amount of money, the big man went home.

313
00:25:02.690 --> 00:25:06.860
The return of Kozuki Oden, Wano's true heir,

314
00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:10.360
was the nation's last hope, so to speak.

315
00:25:10.910 --> 00:25:15.200
But the people's hopes were dashed,
and they were sorely disappointed.

316
00:25:16.620 --> 00:25:20.540
Over time, they became
enraged by his actions.

317
00:25:24.460 --> 00:25:28.170
♪ – It's Kuri's foolish lord, Kozuki Oden! ♪
♪ – It's Kuri's foolish lord, Kozuki Oden! ♪

318
00:25:28.170 --> 00:25:32.050
♪ – The serpent's gaze left him petrified in fear! ♪
♪ – The serpent's gaze left him petrified in fear! ♪

319
00:25:32.050 --> 00:25:33.800
♪ – You lose even if you sneer! ♪
♪ – You lose even if you sneer! ♪

320
00:25:33.800 --> 00:25:35.960
♪ – Let's go, then! ♪
♪ – Let's go, then! ♪

321
00:25:35.970 --> 00:25:39.560
Oden showed up in the capital once a week,

322
00:25:39.560 --> 00:25:43.270
and made a fool of himself
in front of the castle for a pittance.

323
00:25:44.610 --> 00:25:45.860
Even on rainy days.

324
00:25:47.280 --> 00:25:48.490
Or windy days.

325
00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:51.200
Or snowy days.

326
00:25:57.160 --> 00:25:59.120
We are begging you, Lord Oden!

327
00:25:59.540 --> 00:26:02.000
Please tell us the truth!

328
00:26:02.000 --> 00:26:04.250
What did you discuss with Orochi?!

329
00:26:04.250 --> 00:26:05.880
Why are you doing this?!

330
00:26:06.290 --> 00:26:11.630
Even your most loyal followers
in Kuri have given up on you.

331
00:26:12.050 --> 00:26:15.010
Every week, I dance in my
underwear to earn money.

332
00:26:15.010 --> 00:26:17.930
That is my job!

333
00:26:18.810 --> 00:26:21.890
Word of his antics in the capital
had also reached Kuri.

334
00:26:23.440 --> 00:26:27.730
♪ Daikon, ganmo, chikuwa, and eggs! ♪

335
00:26:27.730 --> 00:26:32.030
♪ Konnyaku, chikuwabu, hanpen, and potatoes! ♪

336
00:26:32.030 --> 00:26:37.030
Oh, don't forget shirataki noodles, too!

337
00:26:38.330 --> 00:26:40.500
Don't grow up to be like him!

338
00:26:40.500 --> 00:26:41.660
He's pathetic!

339
00:26:41.660 --> 00:26:46.670
A real samurai would commit seppuku
before becoming Orochi's dog!

340
00:26:46.670 --> 00:26:51.090
♪ Konbu, important! Life, important! ♪

341
00:26:51.090 --> 00:26:54.970
♪ The stock decides the flavor of the broth! ♪

342
00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:03.810
A year later...

343
00:27:11.070 --> 00:27:15.530
after receiving a foreign newspaper
from Shogun Orochi, Oden...

344
00:27:28.290 --> 00:27:35.220
ran along the seacoast, cried out loud,
then, laughed... and cried again...

345
00:27:42.060 --> 00:27:43.930
Roger!

346
00:27:53.530 --> 00:27:56.110
Twenty-four years before the present day...

347
00:27:56.110 --> 00:28:00.780
the world was sent into a frenzy at
the execution of Pirate King Gold Roger.

348
00:28:01.700 --> 00:28:07.540
Eager to obtain the enormous wealth
and the great treasure One Piece he left behind,

349
00:28:07.540 --> 00:28:11.840
all sorts of people took to the sea.

350
00:28:13.760 --> 00:28:17.300
That was the beginning of the Great Pirate Era.

351
00:28:32.820 --> 00:28:34.690
Roger!

352
00:28:37.700 --> 00:28:41.070
You were incredible!

353
00:28:45.040 --> 00:28:48.120
Your whole life was incredible!

354
00:28:54.340 --> 00:28:57.920
Two years after Oden's return to Wano,

355
00:28:57.920 --> 00:29:03.260
a battle between the Gecko Pirates
and the Beast Pirates broke out in Ringo.

356
00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:06.810
Their captains, Gecko Moria
and Kaido, clashed.

357
00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:08.690
Go to hell!

358
00:29:14.900 --> 00:29:17.150
At the same time...

359
00:29:18.150 --> 00:29:21.360
the grave of Ryuma,
God of the Blade, was vandalized.

360
00:29:22.030 --> 00:29:24.910
And even under these circumstances...

361
00:29:24.910 --> 00:29:27.790
♪ Oh, daikon, ganmo! ♪

362
00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:32.960
Oden continued his weekly dance
in the Flower Capital.

363
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:34.540
I wanna dance, too!

364
00:29:34.540 --> 00:29:35.630
Cut it out.

365
00:29:35.630 --> 00:29:39.470
♪ The stock decides the flavor of the broth! ♪

366
00:29:39.470 --> 00:29:42.260
♪ Oden was meant... ♪

367
00:29:42.260 --> 00:29:51.600
Hakumai

368
00:29:42.840 --> 00:29:46.850
♪ to boil! ♪

369
00:29:47.390 --> 00:29:49.520
It's that fool of a lord again.

370
00:29:49.520 --> 00:29:51.600
I feel sorry for the people of Kuri.

371
00:29:52.100 --> 00:29:54.230
The foolish lord of Kuri, huh?

372
00:29:55.650 --> 00:29:58.530
He's undeserving of even being called a lord.

373
00:29:59.570 --> 00:30:01.700
Hey, wait, Hiyori!

374
00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:02.490
No!

375
00:30:02.490 --> 00:30:04.450
I said wait!

376
00:30:05.200 --> 00:30:09.450
I finally made my family targets of scorn...

377
00:30:09.450 --> 00:30:11.160
Father!

378
00:30:12.120 --> 00:30:14.130
I love your dance!

379
00:30:14.960 --> 00:30:16.500
As do I!

380
00:30:20.090 --> 00:30:21.220
Toki...

381
00:30:21.220 --> 00:30:22.220
Yes?

382
00:30:22.220 --> 00:30:23.590
Do you want to leave me?

383
00:30:23.590 --> 00:30:26.550
Is that a joke, or are you
trying to make me mad?

384
00:30:28.140 --> 00:30:29.720
The foolish lord of Kuri.

385
00:30:29.720 --> 00:30:33.190
All of Wano called him so,

386
00:30:33.690 --> 00:30:38.070
and only his family, retainers, and a few
supporters would speak with him.

387
00:30:38.070 --> 00:30:43.200
Are you all still content
with serving as my retainers?

388
00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:45.820
Where else would we be?
Oden Castle

Kuri

389
00:30:45.820 --> 00:30:50.080
We have seen Lord Oden's
naked dance since the olden days.

390
00:30:50.080 --> 00:30:52.750
Yeah! It's meowthing new!

391
00:30:57.670 --> 00:31:00.130
You wanna see Boss Hyogoro?!

392
00:31:00.130 --> 00:31:01.420
Whoa, whoa!

393
00:31:01.420 --> 00:31:03.720
Stay away from him, you fool of a lord!

394
00:31:03.720 --> 00:31:04.930
Stop it!

395
00:31:05.430 --> 00:31:07.390
– Ouch!
– Ouch!

396
00:31:07.390 --> 00:31:09.970
Don't get cocky! Stand aside!

397
00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:11.100
Ma'am!

398
00:31:11.100 --> 00:31:12.180
Got it!

399
00:31:12.180 --> 00:31:13.480
My lady!

400
00:31:13.480 --> 00:31:15.310
My apologies.

401
00:31:15.310 --> 00:31:18.230
Now come in and have some tea!

402
00:31:18.230 --> 00:31:21.110
Hyo! Oden's here!

403
00:31:23.030 --> 00:31:25.950
Orochi won't leave me alone!

404
00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:28.830
Who would wanna serve a guy like that?

405
00:31:30.660 --> 00:31:33.540
At least stay away from danger, Hyo!

406
00:31:33.540 --> 00:31:35.620
I saw you the other day.

407
00:31:35.620 --> 00:31:38.920
Oden, you're getting better at dancing.

408
00:31:38.920 --> 00:31:40.840
Oh please, my lady!

409
00:31:44.170 --> 00:31:46.550
Come on. Have another cup!

410
00:31:46.550 --> 00:31:49.430
Three years pass.

411
00:31:49.430 --> 00:31:51.930
♪ Oh, daikon, ganmo... ♪

412
00:31:53.430 --> 00:31:55.140
♪ chikuwa and eggs! ♪

413
00:31:55.140 --> 00:31:57.270
Look, he's here again this week.

414
00:31:57.270 --> 00:32:01.440
In this snow? He's a helpless fool of a lord.
♪ One, two, three, go ahead and eat! ♪

415
00:32:03.150 --> 00:32:06.110
The snow is killing me...

416
00:32:06.110 --> 00:32:07.070
Shame on you!

417
00:32:07.070 --> 00:32:08.780
You're disgusting!

418
00:32:08.780 --> 00:32:09.870
So annoying.

419
00:32:09.870 --> 00:32:10.530
Go away!

420
00:32:11.200 --> 00:32:16.000
Four years passed in the blink of an eye,
but nothing changed in Wano.

421
00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:21.250
In the fifth year, Orochi made a move.

422
00:32:24.550 --> 00:32:28.050
It's the shogun! Shogun Orochi!

423
00:32:53.660 --> 00:32:57.040
It's been a while, Oden.

424
00:32:57.460 --> 00:33:02.500
I'd like to build several weapons factories here.

425
00:33:03.340 --> 00:33:06.510
I need your cooperation, Oden.

426
00:33:06.510 --> 00:33:09.760
Well, Shogun, what about the ship?

427
00:33:09.760 --> 00:33:12.180
About the promise you and Kaido made–

428
00:33:13.970 --> 00:33:15.640
What are you talking about?!

429
00:33:19.890 --> 00:33:26.440
Forcing everyone here to labor in
these factories day in and day out...

430
00:33:26.440 --> 00:33:29.700
would certainly improve productivity!

431
00:33:29.700 --> 00:33:30.610
Right?!

432
00:33:33.030 --> 00:33:34.620
We'll make Wano...

433
00:33:35.700 --> 00:33:39.250
a weapons manufacturing hub!

434
00:33:43.250 --> 00:33:46.250
P-Please wait!

435
00:33:47.000 --> 00:33:49.630
Oh, yeah, by the way...

436
00:33:49.630 --> 00:33:54.010
Hyogoro was too much for me to handle...

437
00:33:54.010 --> 00:33:56.060
so I left him to Kaido.

438
00:33:56.060 --> 00:33:56.890
What?!

439
00:33:58.520 --> 00:34:03.980
I wanted to have the ruler of Wano's
underworld under my thumb, but I gave up.

440
00:34:03.980 --> 00:34:06.940
Well, he'll probably die soon.

441
00:34:08.320 --> 00:34:11.110
Annoyingly enough, his men tried to stop us.

442
00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:13.240
Give us back our boss!

443
00:34:15.370 --> 00:34:17.620
So it took more effort than we expected.

444
00:34:17.620 --> 00:34:19.540
Oh, yeah.

445
00:34:21.710 --> 00:34:25.840
Speaking of which, remember
Hyogoro's old bag of a wife?!

446
00:34:25.840 --> 00:34:29.590
I heard she screamed
and threw herself on them, too!

447
00:34:29.590 --> 00:34:31.510
My men shot her to death!

448
00:34:32.300 --> 00:34:34.550
No!

449
00:34:34.550 --> 00:34:35.930
Stop it!

450
00:34:35.930 --> 00:34:38.470
Don't take him away!

451
00:34:41.230 --> 00:34:43.480
Hyo...

452
00:34:49.360 --> 00:34:53.240
You'd think that the wife of
a yakuza boss would know better!

453
00:34:56.200 --> 00:34:59.080
By the way, your children...

454
00:34:59.080 --> 00:35:01.040
Momonosuke and Hiyori...

455
00:35:01.580 --> 00:35:03.620
How old are they now?

456
00:35:03.620 --> 00:35:06.170
Children are cute, huh?

457
00:35:06.170 --> 00:35:10.380
They must be absolutely precious now.

458
00:35:10.380 --> 00:35:12.550
Take good care of them.

459
00:35:15.800 --> 00:35:19.140
I leave the construction
of the factories to you!

460
00:35:44.160 --> 00:35:47.250
As his family and retainers had expected,

461
00:35:47.250 --> 00:35:54.380
this great samurai has shouldered
a great burden all alone for five long years.

462
00:36:03.810 --> 00:36:05.480
Orochi...

463
00:36:06.560 --> 00:36:08.190
and Kaido...

464
00:36:08.190 --> 00:36:09.560
We shall end them!

465
00:36:15.860 --> 00:36:20.950
We have been waiting for you
to say that all this time!

466
00:36:24.200 --> 00:36:26.330
Let us go to his island!

467
00:36:27.330 --> 00:36:32.550
While he sleeps off a night of
drinking, we shall take his head!

468
00:36:35.550 --> 00:36:37.720
You are about to witness...

469
00:36:40.800 --> 00:36:47.060
Kozuki Oden's greatest uproar,
for which all of Wano wept.

470
00:36:47.810 --> 00:36:51.860
He stood with his nine samurai,
whom he had taken under his wing.

471
00:36:52.730 --> 00:36:54.280
It was twilight.

472
00:36:55.070 --> 00:37:01.700
The bright red sun lit up their backs
like flames as they marched.

473
00:37:01.700 --> 00:37:06.500
Even the swords at their waists
displayed fiery souls.

474
00:37:08.330 --> 00:37:12.130
The people later honored their intense loyalty,

475
00:37:12.130 --> 00:37:15.920
and called them the Nine Red Scabbards.

476
00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:17.720
My jump is far higher than yours!

477
00:37:17.720 --> 00:37:20.890
No, mine is higher!

478
00:37:25.510 --> 00:37:30.020
Their enemy was Kaido. With only
one target in mind, they marched.

479
00:37:30.020 --> 00:37:32.020
But this is sadly a thing of the past.

480
00:37:32.860 --> 00:37:36.530
What awaits them is
Kozuki Oden's public execution.

481
00:37:45.240 --> 00:37:48.580
Until the Hour of Legend that
would be retold for generations...

482
00:37:49.250 --> 00:37:53.830
please do not blink as you
witness this spectacle!
